            <h2><strong style="color: black;">How to add a Project</strong></h2>

            <hr></hr>

            <!--Step 1-->
            <div style="background-color: #e3e4eb; padding: 1rem;">
                <h4>Step 1</h4>
                <img src="../images/step1ap.png" style="height: 70px;" alt="Step one image">
                <p style="margin-top: 2rem;">
                    -First, click on the add project icon located on the sidebar.
                </p>  
            </div>
            
            <br></br>

            <!--Step 2-->
            <div style="background-color: #e3e4eb; padding: 1rem;">
                <h4>Step 2</h4>
                <img src="../images/step2ap.png" style="height: 300px;" alt="Step two image">
                <p style="margin-top: 2rem;">-Fill out the contact info.</p> 
                <p>-Input the name of the project in the Project Name section.</p>
                <p>-Input the DRN number and the STC/DRV number if applicable.</p>
                <p>-Input the main contact email of the contractor for this close-out. All automated emails will be sent to this email address by default.</p>
                <p>-Input the Close-out Start date in the format of MM/DD/YY. If the date is not added in this format, the project will not be added.</p>
            </div>

            <br></br>

            <!--Step 3-->
            <div style="background-color: #e3e4eb; padding: 1rem;">
                <h4>Step 3</h4>
                <img src="../images/step3-1ap.png" style="height: 350px; margin-right: 3rem;" alt="Step two image">
                <img src="../images/step3-2ap.png" style="height: 350px;" alt="Step two image">
                <p style="margin-top: 2rem;">-Go through the check boxes and click all that apply to the project being added.</p>
                <p>-If a box does not apply to the project being added, do not check the box.</p>
                <p>-If the first box is checked, additional boxes will appear as seen in figure two. Click all that apply.</p>  
            </div>
            
            <br></br>

            <!--Step 4-->
            <div style="background-color: #e3e4eb; padding: 1rem;">
                <h4>Step 4</h4>
                <img src="../images/step4ap.png" style="height: 50px;" alt="Step two image">
                <p style="margin-top: 2rem;">-Review all fields and then click the "Add Project" button.</p>
                <p>-If you have any of the contact fields filled out incorrectly, the project will not be added.</p>   
            </div>
            
            <br></br>

            <!--Step 5-->
            <div style="background-color: #e3e4eb; padding: 1rem;">
                <h4>Step 5</h4>
                <img src="../images/step5ap.png" style="height: 150px;" alt="Step two image">
                <p style="margin-top: 2rem;">-If all is correct, the project will be added and you will be redirected to the "My Projects" page.</p>
                <p>-If you left the first checkbox blank, you will be asked about sending an automated email for the initial contact to the contractor.</p>
                <p>-If you wish to have KeepUp send an email to the contractor, click the "ok" button and you will be redirected to a page where you will review and edit the email before it is sent.</p>
                <p>-If you wish to not send the initial email, click the "cancle" button, the project will be added and you will be redirected to the "My Projects" page.</p>       
            </div>
            
            <br></br>

            <!--Step 5-->
            <div style="background-color: #e3e4eb; padding: 1rem;">
                <h4>Step 6 *Optional*</h4>
                <img src="../images/step6ap.png" style="height: 300px;" alt="Step two image">
                <p style="margin-top: 2rem;">-If you clicked the "ok" button, you will be redirected to view the email that will be sent to the contractor.</p>
                <p>-At this point, you will review the email and edit any information necessary as well as add any colleagues to the email via the "add colleagues" button.</p>
                <p>-The email will NOT send until you attach an affidavit in .pdf format.</p>    
                <p>-Once you have reviewed the email, you can click send and the project will be added.</p>
                <p>-After the email is sent, you will be redirected to the "my projects" page.</p>
            </div>
         

